description:
File: rust/lichen-rpl/src/trickle.rs
Line: 127-128

The heard_consistent() method increments counter without overflow protection:
```rust
pub fn heard_consistent(&mut self) {
    self.counter += 1;
}
```

Impact: In extremely long-running scenarios with many consistent transmissions, the counter could overflow u32. While unlikely in practice (would require >4 billion consistent messages in one Trickle interval), this violates the principle of no silent overflows in safety-critical networking code.

More importantly, an attacker could flood a node with consistent messages to trigger this overflow, potentially causing the counter to wrap to 0 and enabling suppressed transmissions (counter < k would become true again).

Fix: Use saturating_add:
```rust
pub fn heard_consistent(&mut self) {
    self.counter = self.counter.saturating_add(1);
}
```
